## ✅ Phase 1 — The Flask App (COMPLETE)

Created 3 files and pushed to GitHub:

**`app.py`** — minimal Flask app with two routes:
```python
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def home():
    return {"status": "ok", "message": "Hello from CI/CD pipeline!"}

@app.route("/health")
def health():
    return {"status": "healthy"}, 200

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(host="0.0.0.0", port=5000)
```

**`test_app.py`** — two pytest tests, one per route:
```python
from app import app

def test_home():
    client = app.test_client()
    res = client.get("/")
    assert res.status_code == 200

def test_health():
    client = app.test_client()
    res = client.get("/health")
    assert res.status_code == 200
```

**`requirements.txt`**
```
flask
pytest
```

**Tests verified locally:**
```
test_app.py::test_home   PASSED
test_app.py::test_health PASSED
2 passed in 0.20s
```

